sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as rhods-operator
    participant NotebookCtrl as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant kubelet as kubelet
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AuthProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Workbench as Workbench Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 1: Image Registration
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply ImageStream manifests<br/>(kustomize overlay)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: ImageStreams created

    Note over User,Workbench: Flow 2: Workbench Discovery & Launch
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: List ImageStreams<br/>(read annotations)
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Available workbench images
    User->>Dashboard: Select workbench image<br/>Auth: OAuth/OIDC
    Dashboard-->>User: Display workbench options
    User->>Dashboard: Create Notebook CR
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CRs<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>NotebookCtrl: New Notebook event
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Pod + inject auth sidecar<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    kubelet->>Registry: Pull workbench image<br/>Auth: Pull secret
    Registry-->>kubelet: Container image layers

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Workbench Access
    User->>AuthProxy: Access workbench UI<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer token
    AuthProxy->>Workbench: Forward to JupyterLab<br/>HTTP/8888, plaintext<br/>Auth: None (localhost)
    Workbench-->>AuthProxy: JupyterLab UI response
    AuthProxy-->>User: Proxied response

    Note over Workbench,S3: Flow 4: Notebook Data Access
    Workbench->>S3: Read/write data (Boto3)<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS credentials
    S3-->>Workbench: Data objects
    Workbench->>K8sAPI: oc CLI commands<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over Registry,S3: Flow 5: Elyra Pipeline Runtime
    Note right of Registry: Data Science Pipelines<br/>pulls runtime image
    Registry-->>Workbench: Runtime container image
    Note right of Workbench: Runtime executes<br/>pipeline node
    Workbench->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS credentials
